summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming previous resolutions 242, 338, 1397, 1402, and 1403, 
Reiterating grave concern at violent events since September 2000 and situation deterioration,
Condemning terrorist attacks, including bombings in Israel and a Palestinian school,
Gravely concerned at reoccupation of Ramallah and Palestinian cities, 
Demanding immediate end to reoccupation and severe restrictions,
 Reiterating need for respect of international humanitarian law,

1. Demands complete cessation of violence, terror, provocation, incitement, and destruction;
2. Demands Israel cease measures in and around Ramallah, including destruction of infrastructure;
3. Demands expeditious withdrawal of Israeli forces from Palestinian cities to pre-September 2000 positions;
4. Calls on Palestinian Authority to bring those responsible for terrorist acts to justice;
5. Expresses full support for Quartet efforts, calls for cooperation, and recognizes Arab League Beirut Summit initiative;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
